mxCell.value: ^^xsd:string "The Achaemenid Reliefs"
^^xsd:string "550 BCE - 330 BCE"

^^xsd:string "The Achaemenid Reliefs are a remarkable aspect of ancient Persian art and architecture, primarily associated with the Achaemenid Empire, which was founded by Cyrus the Great and lasted until its conquest by Alexander the Great. These reliefs are some of the most significant artistic legacies of the Achaemenid Empire, in particular for for its cultural and historical importance, which offers a glimpse into the political, cultural, and religious life of ancient Persia ."
^^xsd:string "Persepolis (Iran), Aechemenid Art, Iranian history."
^^xsd:string "Sculpture, Relief"
